#By default Root has no the SSH permission ... 

 >>> service ssh status | start | stop .... 

 #we have to give the root the ssh permission . 

 >>> service ssh start 

 >>> sudo nano /etc/ssh/sshd_config 

 #uncomment this line - PermitRootLogin yes , and password authentication yes, UsePAM yes. then save 

 >>> sudo ssh restart.

 >>> sudo password root 
 >>>> ssh localhost 
 >>>> now get access the ssh . 
 >>> exit | 'exit from ssh root shell'.


